x4freetext: The K-400 Intense Neutron Generator
Three disc-shaped samples (diameter: 14.0 mm,
thickness: 1.4 mm) were made by using thorium oxide
powder which have a purity of 99.95%. The three
samples were installed at ~3.5 cm from the T-Ti
target and at 0 deg, 45 deg and 90 deg relative to
the incident deuteron beam.
The gamma-ray activity of samples was measured
with a well calibrated HPGe-gamma detector. The
HPGe-gamma detection system has an energy resolution
of 1.7 keV FWHM at 1.33 MeV. The calibration of
energy and efficiency was carried out by the
standard: 241Am, 60Co, 137Cs and 152Eu. A
recalibration was performed also for the dead time,
because of the high activities in the irradiated
samples due to large number of fission nuclides. The
correction between software output and count loss
from the HPGe-gamma system was re-estimated with a
jamming gamma-source (137Cs).
Total uncertainty (6.5%-15.6%)
statistical uncertainty (1.2%-2.8%)
The detection efficiency (~1.5%)
The samples weighting (<0.1%)
The half-life of the reaction products
The intensity of gamma-ray from NuDat
Corrections were made for the geometric correction,
the selfabsorption correction, the gamma cascade
correction and the multiple fission nuclides.
Compiled by Lile Liu (CNDC)
